content:
Configure Dashboard Data Visibility in Salesforce Classic

To specify which data to display in a dashboard, select a running user.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
View My Teamâ€™s Dashboards or View All Data

Edit a dashboard. Next to View dashboard as, click .

Select a running user type.
Run as specified user: The dashboard uses the security settings of the specified user.
  To see all available users, enter *.

Run as logged-in user: The dashboard viewer sees data based on their own access to data.

To enable viewers with permission to change the running user, select Let authorized users change running user. Click OK.
For View dashboard as, enter a running user. Save your changes.
title: Configure Dashboard Data Visibility in Salesforce Classic
